title: Tom Petty and The Heartbreakers 1989-09-13 Chapel Hill, NC FLAC
description:
Tom Petty & The Heartbreakers 1989-09-13 Chapel Hill, NC FLAC

Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers
September 13, 1989
Dean's Dome, University of North Carolina,
Chapel Hill, NC
Plus bonus tracks from: August 20, 1989, 
Garden State Arts Center,  Holmdel, NJ  
Pluto Records - PLO 9132 - SB 6
FM Broadcast Recording, excellent quality
(Bonus tracks from Audience recording, very good quality

Track List: (FM BROADCAST RECORDING)
 1. Bye Bye Johnny (C. Berry)
 2. The Damage You've Done
 3. Breakdown
 4. Free Fallin'
 5. The Waiting
 6. Benmont's Boogie
 7. Don't Come Around Here No More
 8. Southern Accents
 9. Even the Losers (Acoustic)
10. Listen to the Heart (Acoustic)
11. A Face in the Crowd (Acoustic)
12. Something Big
13. I Won't Back Down
14. I Need to Know
15. Refugee
16. Running Down a Dream 

Bonus Tracks (1989-08-20 - Holmdel, NJ) 
AUDIENCE RECORDING BONUS TRACKS (Very Good)
17.  I'll Feel A Whole Lot Better (Byrds)
18.  How Many More Days
19. Yer So Bad (Acoustic)
20. You Got Lucky
21. Rebels
22. Should I Stay Or Should I Go? (The Clash)
23. Jammin' Me

Note: This show (1989-09-13) has also been widely distributed in various 
bootlegs as being from 1990-05-18 - Wilmington, NC (with titles such as 
Southern Choice, etc.). However, all recordings I've heard attributed to 
this date have been this same recording as 1989-09-13. although I do not 
know for sure the actual correct date, the information I have indicates 
that 1989-09-13 Chapel Hill is the correct date. Actually, the recording 
version I used for this comes from the Southern Choice (Italian) boot, as 
that versipn has a clearer brighter sound (probably earlier generation 
recording) than some other boots ('Lost in North Carolina', 'Free Fallin') 
identified as 1989-09-13
